Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.13,0:01:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Game! First set won by Midorikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.51,0:01:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Game count: 6-2.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.79,0:01:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll defeat her,{/I'm taking it,} Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.24,0:01:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like I already did in the first set.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.19,0:02:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment, my bullet serve \Nis completely invincible{for some reason she uses a slightly modified verb that Oka used for "undermine" but I think it's just a coincidence} to Oka Hiromi{/vanquishes/crashes ... soundly}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.82,0:02:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I have scored 16 consecutive service-aces.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.43,0:02:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi is still too inexperienced \Nto undermine{this word does not fit very well from her lips but I'm sticking to my previous convictions} my serve even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.46,0:02:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch as I earn this victory, Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.26,0:02:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My bullet serve has been revived{/resuscitated better fits the context but revived sound better in the episode name}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This heavy 180 gram ball... \NI was hitting and hitting it day after day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.79,0:02:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,While sending the ball, I thought of Jin,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.64,0:02:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard Jin's voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.90,0:02:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No offense, Jin, \Nbut my true target is not Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.10,0:02:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Madame Butterfly, waiting for me \Nin the round two - Ryuzaki Reika.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.92,0:02:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Hiromi prostrates under my serve again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.95,0:02:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Jin. Because you raised her{guess - ikonda} yourself, \NI know Hiromi will probably catch up with me soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.75,0:02:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But before that{/first}, I'm gonna have to get \Njust one step ahead of her.{/make just a small headway over her}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.47,0:02:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Game: Midorikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.03,0:02:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.87,0:02:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.04,0:02:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.19,0:03:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is Midorikawa's service-game again. \NIf Oka doesn't return a single one, the match is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.11,0:03:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If Oka doesn't break through the bullet serve now, \Nit would be a complete defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.31,0:03:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Not decided{/we don't know} yet. \NNothing is decided yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.99,0:03:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the very last ball \Ncan turn the tide of match.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.21,0:03:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka is the kind of player \Nto hold such potential.{/This exact kind of possibility may be hidden in Oka.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.59,0:03:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That was exactly \Nwhy Munakata noticed her and brought her up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.10,0:03:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To the very last game... \NTo the very last ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.60,0:03:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata believed in it, \Nwe believe in it.{maybe a present tense would fit better}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.79,0:03:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And because Oka herself believes so too, \Nit all began{ in the first place} and came to this point{added; unsure, maybe "because Oka believes, everything is just starting now"}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.90,0:03:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, even if she should lose this match, \Nif Oka never finds a way{added},
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.94,0:03:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,she will still make sure to show everyone here, \Nwhat she's worth{/Lit: show us something}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.51,0:03:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if for a moment, \Nshe will show us her brilliance.{Lit: something, certainly... with a momentary flash of light​, she'll show something brilliant/will be glistening}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.30,0:03:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.37,0:03:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFEFDFF&\bord11\blur11\3c&HFFA958&\t(0,1000,\bord0\blur0.4\c&HF2E7E9&\3c&HF1AF5E&)\fnGabriola\fs90\pos(320,340)}Episode 13\N\N\N{\fs90}I'm Sure... He's Watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.01,0:03:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A little more...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.01,0:03:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I need just a little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.75,0:04:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, I'm starting to read the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.11,0:04:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also getting used to the speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.78,0:04:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What lacks{/only thing left} is timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.07,0:04:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I just need to adjust to{/match/meet} her timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.39,0:04:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,30-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.82,0:04:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.39,0:04:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,40-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.07,0:04:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Match point: Midorikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.79,0:04:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How unfortunate!\NJust as she finally managed{/started} to receive it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:04:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So close...{I'm not sure what hoshi stands for here} \NYou really deserved to score it{/better/that was really regrettable}, Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.78,0:05:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Still... Still, Hiromi, at least with this one shot{/with at least one ball}, \Ngive her a hard time{guess, no clue what kanshiteyanna is}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.47,0:05:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's match-point already.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.23,0:05:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're this one point away from losing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.01,0:05:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, why does nothing in life{half-guess} \Never goes the smooth way?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Chiba, I want you to archive this game for me \Nin its fullest.{/I'm sure, she saved the best of her performance for the final part/record in properly all the way until the conclusion - guess because I don't hear "record", only "put for later for me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.93,0:05:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter if she wins or loses,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.55,0:05:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for Oka, there will never be a{/another day will never come when she can play a} second match \Nlike this one she is playing today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.02,0:05:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.71,0:05:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a bit disheartened{/fell into a little depression/got carried away}. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.01,0:05:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. If I don't capture it, \Nthen who else will?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.30,0:05:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka's today... \NAs well as the rest of Oka's days...{ from now on}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.02,0:05:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,One more ball. \NJust one more ball, Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.54,0:05:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.04,0:05:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, I will send this final ball back! Certainly!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.64,0:05:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.23,0:06:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I just need to hit one last ball!{/That was just one final hit!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.91,0:06:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.77,0:06:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.19,0:06:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Player Midorikawa \Nis unable to continue the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.15,0:06:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, this match's winner becomes {player }Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.34,0:06:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3}Whatever you make{/think} of it{/is the reason/pretext}, \Na victory is a victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.46,0:06:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3}Next is battle with Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, about Midorikawa... \NYou think she'll be alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears her special training with a heavy 180 gram ball \Nhas taken a heavy toll{/messed up/tattered} on Ranko's right wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.43,0:06:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be worried. \NNothing of that is your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.73,0:07:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it! Instead, focus more \Non your upcoming battle with Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.11,0:07:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What if... What if she never manages \Nto recover from that condition{/she won't be able to recover just like that}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.59,0:07:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I do? After all, Midorikawa \Nis experiencing the same thing as me.{/is just like me/in the same sircumstances as me}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.44,0:07:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as she finally escaped{/passed} that dark tunnel... \NJust as she returned to the light...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.83,0:07:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.75,0:07:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Come inside, \NI've been waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.49,0:07:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.07,0:07:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Before your tomorrow's battle with Ryuzaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.07,0:07:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,she wanted to meet you, by all means.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.37,0:08:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard many talks \Nabout how much you're worried for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.79,0:08:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... How could I not be? \NAfter what happened to your right...{/How is it looking for your right hand?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.38,0:08:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure, soon, \Nit would be able to wield{/hold} a racket again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.99,0:08:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It certainly would! Wouldn't it?{/Right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.36,0:08:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The {doctor's }diagnosis was pretty clear. \NNo longer an option{It's a nonstarter already}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.99,0:08:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,My right hand \Nis now completely useless for tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.27,0:08:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't be helped. I'm reaping the consequence \Nof my own rash decision.{/I decided it myself and conducted my special training myself}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.55,0:08:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,At least I know I did my utmost \Nto defeat you and Madame Butterfly.{/I thought it'd help me ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.38,0:08:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I regret nothing.{/I have no regrets.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.75,0:08:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.11,0:08:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Munakata...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.71,0:08:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Please save her... \NYou have to save Midorikawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.91,0:08:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all alright, no worries. \NHave no worries just like I do!{/I personally have ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.22,0:08:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There, see? There, there! \NI still have my whole left hand on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.82,0:08:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.86,0:09:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Though it can probably take a while, but I made a decision: \Nreborn as a southpaw, I'll give it a fresh start{/another shot}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.15,0:09:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, whatever is to come, \Nremember - I haven't given up on my tennis yet!{/you can already be assured you didn't make me abandon tennis/just like me, don't throw away your tennis - unsure}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.23,0:09:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No way I ever give up on it.{/I don't even think of giving it up.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.67,0:09:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore... Therefore, just like me... No,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.16,0:09:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,just like all of us, with exception to Jin,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.18,0:09:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you still have a plenty of time ahead of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.11,0:09:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best at tomorrow's match.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.69,0:09:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,On my behalf too, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.68,0:09:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi, I would gladly face you{/come at me/over} \Nwith all you've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.84,0:09:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it won't start pouring \Nin the middle of a match.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.83,0:10:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.06,0:10:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you have a good sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you were still playing piano \Nvery late into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.87,0:10:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. \NFather, I must have disturbed your sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.01,0:10:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No, quite conversely.{/I didn't say that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.01,0:10:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, listening to your piano \Nworks like a sedative for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.86,0:10:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Inadvertently, it became a splendid lullaby for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.95,0:10:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing the piano
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.37,0:10:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,allows me to process many thoughts \Nin the meantime.{/While ... I think of many different things}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.29,0:10:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Like those of tennis \NI've been playing since I was six and to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.53,0:10:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Of countless{/One after another} matches, \Nnumerous awards{/each one ending with triumph}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Time after time, without any bitter afterthoughts{/regrets}, \NI burst into flames on the court until I burn my life out.{/unsure, maybe "I ignited myself in an all-engulfing flame on the court until I burn out everything I have" like a vague ANJ reference, or "I burned up and burned out on the court, sacrificing everything to the flame"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.54,0:10:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My opponents change, \Ntime and place differ as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.34,0:10:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What remains the same is myself!{/Where no alteration happens is in me!/Only I persist always the same}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.35,0:10:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fight of Ryuzaki Reika against herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.95,0:10:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have always been coming here{/approaching the match} \Nwith this conviction in mind and heart.{/Lit: Thinking this way and settled on that mindset in my heart, I finally came}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet this time it's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.91,0:10:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's match is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.98,0:10:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This time{ in my heart}, I need to live up to the expectations \Nof many people{/many people settled ... /I'm facing a whole caboodle of people/Lit: In my heart I'm accepting various people - unsure about accepting, maybe "Many people are on my mind/settled in my heart" or "together with me"}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.73,0:11:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The expectations of Midorikawa Ranko,\Nof Coach Munakata...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.07,0:11:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, to Hiromi's expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.35,0:11:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to this point, I have always felt \Nlike there's no one else but me on the court.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.74,0:11:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time, it's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika, you should think of this as a usual match, \Nthe same as all the previous ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.33,0:11:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.06,0:11:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I will have to disobey this one, father{/there is no way I could do such a thing}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.09,0:11:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.87,0:11:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, I don't feel left out \Ncompletely alone on the court.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.50,0:11:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something I never experienced{/that never happened to me} before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.63,0:11:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To think that on the court, where only victory or defeat ever had any significance{/nothing but ... ever mattered}, I would feel {something like }a human warmth!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.67,0:11:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.21,0:11:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why Hiromi is so amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.89,0:11:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike me, she has probably been experiencing{/Lit:because she knew something like that since the time she was starting to play tennis} that \Never since when she tried tennis for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.22,0:11:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I managed it{/it was coming to me} so naturally,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.63,0:11:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata Jin preferred Oka Hiromi over me, \Nand I've finally come{/grown} to understand the reason{/as for why he did it}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.48,0:11:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.39,0:11:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been haunting me{/I've been obsessed with it} for those three years -
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.75,0:11:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"Munakata Jin - \Nwhy did he prefer{/favor/choose} Hiromi over me?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.47,0:12:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, I will hardly ever \Nsay this for the second time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.63,0:12:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So please hear me out just once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.99,0:12:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata Jin, save for my father, \Nhas become the first ever person that I{/for me personally}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.51,0:12:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The first person in my whole life,{/since I was born} \Nwhom I held in the highest regard.{/to earn my esteem/that I thought of as "suberb"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.31,0:12:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.99,0:12:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.91,0:12:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.03,0:12:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going there to reap my victory!{/to win}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.82,0:12:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.67,0:13:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.06,0:13:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The one you chose \Nand bet{/entrusted ... to} your everything on, Oka,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.86,0:13:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,on this big stage of All-Japan's Open
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.27,0:13:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is having a face-off with{/fighting} Ryuzaki Reika.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.77,0:13:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In one of your letters of praise{Lit: letter of gratitude i.e. to thank one, I don't see how that makes sense}, \Nyou put{/wrote} it this way for me:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.77,0:13:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oka will conquer the{/'s aim is the} world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.98,0:13:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki Reika is but one big{unsure maybe "one of many walls that"} concrete wall \Nthat Oka will have to break through on her way."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, the reality seems to be a bit different.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.27,0:13:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just about Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.80,0:13:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa Ranko, too, grew frantic \Nabout not letting your selectee Oka break through.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.23,0:13:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They are trying their utmost{/frantically} to pose for Oka \Nmuch thicker, much higher walls than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.43,0:13:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That minuscule sapling you planted in Oka, \Nnow grows not just in Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.44,0:13:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In{side} Ryuzaki and Midorikawa too, \Nit starts to take root.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.60,0:13:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I would go as far as saying, it has probably already sprouted{/sent out shoots; no clue what is "me" here} in the rest of our bunch as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.39,0:13:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you've bet your everything on tennis alone,{unsure}\Nthrowing it all in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.30,0:13:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, that perilous{/risky/wavering/flickering/hesitating;DeepL suggest "twinkle in your eye" but I don't see how it fits here} wager{guess} of yours{added} \Nis finally starting to pay off{/get rewarded} soundly{/spectacularly/with certainty}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.11,0:13:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They are still hobbling in zigzags,{no fukcing clue, Lit: dangerous/risky is at least/no little than, maybe "they take every precaution needed" or "they're still wary of it" but I couldn't do any better than to make a reference to OP song, though the second line with "stepping on a marsh" from there would do just as fine}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.15,0:14:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but move steadily towards their limitless potential!{/those guys hold an infinity of possibilities; maybe just 1 guy since he only means Oka}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.31,0:14:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Deuce!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.11,0:14:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We can{/have no choice} but to watch them silently{ from the side}, Munakata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.29,0:14:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Both Oka and Ryuzaki are using up \Nall the power in their possession.{/exert themselves to the full capacity of their power/putting out all of the power they have}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.56,0:15:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Particularly Oka - by whichever course the ball comes, \Nshe is trying to catch up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.98,0:15:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In whichever position it reaches her{/from whichever stance; unclear, maybe "from this kind of posture"}, \Njust like you taught her to, she is trying to nail an ace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.96,0:15:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, I'm convinced{/can finally guarantee/understand/I know what I'm talking about} her body \Nremembered{unclear maybe "moves this way"} to do that{second word is totally unclear} reflexively{/naturally}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.25,0:15:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You did a splendid job, Munakata.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,While Oka keeps on playing matches like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.43,0:15:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,while she puts herself out \Nfor{/bring ... against/unleashes ...} superb opponents like that,{unsure, maybe it's "superb opponents who bring themselves out entirely" and not Oka}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.61,0:15:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka's potential is infinite.{/Lit: The key to Oka's limitless perspectives is ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.74,0:15:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She may have lost yesterday and today,{/even if she lost ...} \Nbut she has all it takes{/requirements/capabilities} to become the ultimate winner{/winner in the end/final winner}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.63,0:15:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata, it was you who chose her, \Nyou who raised her{/brought her up} all the way up to this point.{/and accompanied/brought/directed her all the way here}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.31,0:15:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts to dribble...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.54,0:16:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.34,0:16:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Munakata...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.91,0:16:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.55,0:16:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It was winter when Coach left us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.80,0:16:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,An excruciating spring followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.79,0:17:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, on this rainy court, \NI'm hitting the ball again{added}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.14,0:17:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely focused{/Bring myself out fully}, with all my might, \Nin this one moment of my 18-year-old life,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.82,0:17:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,mindful that each one of those is not like any other{/it never returns the same way again/the second time; it's a continuation of "each ball is different" doctrine from earlier eps}, \NI'm hitting a ball after a ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.43,0:17:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Harsh, yet kind... All the words{ and your voice} I ever heard from you \Nwere full of that kind of duality{added}.{/Lit: were all the words and voice you gave me}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.51,0:17:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Day after day, you kept on looking at \Nme with those benevolent{/warm} eyes{/gaze}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.47,0:17:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And time after time, \Nthis look{I hope it's "look in your eyes" and not something else implied} was never like any other{/never returned again}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.00,0:17:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The warmth{it's different word for warmth from 2 lines back} of someone very dear I've lost \Nis still here with me,{unsure maybe "the warmth that someone very dear bequeathed to me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and with one after another ball \NI'm hitting wholeheartedly,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.99,0:17:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this fire inside me is burning brighter \Nwith ever-growing confidence.{it's actually "the radiance rises/strenghtens with certainty inside my heart to let me hit those balls firmly and with all my might" but my option is no less artistic while is easier to put in words}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.15,0:17:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, can you hear it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.03,0:17:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The upsetting things, the delighting things{/sad or happy something, maybe thoughts or idk} - \Nwhen I put everything in and hit the ball wholeheartedly,{/with each hit that I put my heart and ... in}{it's built a bit tricky and maybe she putting them in her heart and not "togetheer with her heart in a hit"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.93,0:17:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"PON!" - it makes such an uplifting{/great} sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.03,0:18:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Game! Game count: 5-4. \NOka leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.19,0:18:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In the second set,{I don't remember 1 set ending already but there's no room for misinterpretation unless he says "a tie-set"; upd: nvm, the score during prev line shows games in sets and not serves in games} \NOka may break into the lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.80,0:18:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She just needs to take one more game \Nto bring the set count to tie with 1-1!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.43,0:18:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish this match would last forever, \Nwith neither of the sides losing or winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.43,0:18:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In this particular match,{/If we only speak about this match,} there has to be a winner, \Nand an only one at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.02,0:18:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the long run{/perspective/outlook}, it's nothing but one point \Nin the initial game of a lifelong match.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.78,0:18:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In two years, three years, \Nmaybe even ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.19,0:18:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the fire{/spirit} of their incredible rivalry, that has just started, \Nwill still burn in a long match with everything on the line!{/those amazing rivals would still be playing this long match that had just started and on which they betted their everything}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.67,0:19:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki, Oka, both players. \NPlease come over for a quick word.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.26,0:19:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We would have probably tolerated the rain,{/now it's not only raining,} \Nbut now a strong wind also picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.77,0:19:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say if we suspend this match{ for now} \Nand finish it tomorrow from where we left off{/reschedule it for later date of tomorrow}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.83,0:19:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish to continue it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.79,0:19:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Oka, what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.83,0:19:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm unanimous with Ms. Ryuzaki{/share ...'s point}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.55,0:19:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.80,0:19:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.15,0:20:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This match, I feel that{added} he is watching it. \NCertainly, from{added} somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.80,0:20:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.48,0:20:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He must be!{/for sure}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.26,0:20:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's do it{/go}, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.55,0:20:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.83,0:20:26.35,Sign,,0,0,0,,Because it was so unbearable,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.05,0:20:30.85,Sign,,0,0,0,,I used to cry by the window
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.85,0:20:38.23,Sign,,0,0,0,,But now, next spring is on my doorstep
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.55,0:20:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.11,0:20:42.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,On the bare branches,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.21,0:20:46.90,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I notice fresh verdure
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.78,0:20:55.32,Sign,,0,0,0,,Still so weak, struggling through the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.33,0:21:03.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Hey, why is it only when one loses something,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.80,0:21:11.71,Sign,,0,0,0,,He gets to see what was going on all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.43,0:21:19.79,Sign,,0,0,0,,Hey, I wonder if you can hear me \Neven while you're not here anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.43,0:21:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll stay forever by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.78,0:21:22.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,So I made a promise
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.78,0:21:24.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,to carry on living my own way,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.65,0:21:31.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,therefore you must also, even if for an eternity,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.91,0:21:35.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,Keep looking after me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.91,0:21:38.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,From your far away
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.79,0:21:43.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,Keep looking after me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.63,0:21:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, meeting you \Nwas the grandest blessing of my life.
